l| location= New York |url=http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-1444351311.html|isbn= 978-1-4443-5131-6}}, 2 vol. 1232 pp; 64 topical chapters by experts; emphasis on historiography.\n* {{cite book| ref= harv | last= Stampp | first= Kenneth M. | title= America in 1857: A Nation on the Brink | url= https://archive.org/details/americain185700kenn | url-access= registration | year= 1990 | publisher= Oxford University Press| location= Oxford, New York |isbn= 978-0-19-503902-3}}\n* {{cite book |last=Stern |first=Phillip Van Doren |title=The Confederate Navy |authorlink=Philip Van Doren Stern |publisher=Doubleday & Company, Inc |year=1962 |isbn= |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=GDeqAAAAIAAJ}} |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv |last1=Symonds|first1=Craig L.|last2=Clipson|first2=William J.|title=The Naval Institute Historical Atlas of the U.S. Navy|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=q_HIcc8n3K4C}}|year=2001|publisher=Naval Institute Press|isbn=978-1-55750-984-0}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last1=Tucker |first1=Spencer C.|last2=Pierpaoli |first2= Paul G.|last3=White |first3=William E.|title= The Civil War Naval Encyclopedia|publisher= ABC-CLIO|year= 2010|location=Santa Barbara, California |isbn=978-1-59884-338-5|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=q4mwAtj2r3UC|page=462}}}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv | last= Varon | first= Elizabeth R. | title= Disunion!: The Coming of the American Civil War, 1789\u20131859 | year= 2008 | publisher= University of North Carolina Press| location= Chapel Hill, North Carolina |isbn= 978-0-8078-3232-5}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last= Vinovskis|first= Maris|title= Toward a Social History of the American Civil War: Exploratory Essays|publisher= Cambridge University Press|year= 1990|location= Cambridge, England|isbn= 978-0-521-39559-5|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=9D4TAwc93VoC}}}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv | last= Ward | first= Geoffrey R. | title= The Civil War: An Illustrated History| year= 1990 | publisher= Alfred A. Knopf | location= New York |isbn= 978-0-394-56285-8}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last=Weeks|first=William E.|title=The New Cambridge History of American Foreign Relations|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=9D4TAwc93VoC}}|year= 2013|publisher= Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge, New York|isbn=978-1-107-00590-7}}\n* {{cite book | ref= harv | last= Weigley | first= Frank Russell | title= A Great Civil War: A Military and Political History, 1861\u20131865 | year= 2004 | publisher= Indiana University Press | location= Bloomington, Indiana | isbn= 978-0-253-33738-2 | url= https://archive.org/details/greatcivilwarmil00russ }}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last1= Welles |first1=Gideon |title= Secretary of the Navy's Report|publisher= American Seamen's Friend Society|year= 1865 |volume=37\u201338 |url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=u4gfAAAAYAAJ|page=152}}}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last1=Winters|first1=John D.|title= The Civil War in Louisiana|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=PjicJWUQhPYC&pg=PR3}} |year=1963|publisher=[[Louisiana State University Press]] |location= Baton Rouge, Louisiana |isbn=978-0-8071-0834-5}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv | last1= Woodworth|first= Steven E.| title= American Civil War: A Handbook of Literature and Research | year= 1996 | publisher= Greenwood Press | location= Wesport, Connecticut |isbn= 978-0-313-29019-0}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Gugliotta, Guy. [https://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/03/science/civil-war-toll-up-by-20-percent-in-new-estimate.html New Estimate Raises Civil War Death Toll], ''[[The New York Times]]'', April 3, 2012, p. D1 (of the New York edition), and April 2, 2012, on NYTimes.com. Retrieved 2012-04-03 online.\n* [[Bibliography of early American naval history#American Civil War|Bibliography of American Civil War naval history]]\n* {{cite EB1911|wstitle=American Civil War |short=x}}\n* {{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=XWyKZwEACAAJ}}|title=The Artillery Service in the War of the Rebellion, 1861\u201365|last=Tidball|first=John C.|date=2011|publisher=Westholme Publishing|isbn=9781594161490|language=en}}\n*The Civil War: A Visual History, [[DK (publisher)|DK]] 2011\n*Weeks, Michael. The Complete Civil War Road Trip Guide: More than 500 Sites from Gettysburg to Vicksburg   Countryman Press 2016\n*Shaara, Jeff. Civil War Battlefields: Discovering America's Hallowed Ground Ballantine Books 2006\n*Edwards,F Laura. A Legal History of the Civil War and Reconstruction: A Nation of Rights  Cambridge University Press 2015 \n*McPherson,M James. The War That Forged a Nation: Why the Civil War Still Matters Oxford University Press 2017\n\n==External links==\n<!--Please:\n1) Follow the [[WP:EL]] guideline where possible and consider discussing on the talk page;\n2) Do not turn these bullets into headers! They expand the TOC too much-->\n* {{curlie|Society/History/By_Region/North_America/United_States/Wars/Civil_War/|American Civil War}}\n* [https://westpoint.edu/academics/academic-departments/history/american-civil-war West Point Atlas of Civil War Battles]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160818205335/http://www.archives.gov/research/civil-war/photos/index.html Civil War photos] at the [[National Archives and Records Administration|National Archives]]\n* [https://www.loc.gov/pictures/search?st=grid&c=100&co=cwp View images] from the [https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/cwp/ Civil War Photographs Collection] at the Library of Congress\n* [http://www.battlefields.org/ American Battlefield Trust] A non-profit land preservation and educational organization with two divisions, the Civil War Trust and the Revolutionary War Trust, dedicated to preserving America's battlefields through land acquisitions.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090811064152/http://www.gettysburg.edu/library/gettdigital/civil_war/civilwar.htm Civil War Era Digital Collection at Gettysburg College] This collection contains digital images of political cartoons, personal papers, pamphlets, maps, paintings a