mi-indef}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=October 2013}}\n{{short description|Internal war in the U.S. over slavery}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = \n| partof      = \n| image       = CivilWarUSAColl.png\n| image_size  = 300px\n| caption     = '''Clockwise from top:'''<br>[[Battle of Gettysburg]], [[Union Army|Union]] [[John C. Tidball|Captain John Tidball's]] [[Field artillery in the American Civil War|artillery]], [[Confederate States Army|Confederate]] prisoners, [[Casemate ironclad|ironclad]] {{USS|Atlanta|1861|6}}, ruins of [[Richmond, Virginia]], [[Battle of Franklin (1864)|Battle of Franklin]]\n| date        = April 12, 1861 \u2013 May 9, 1865{{Efn|[[CSS Shenandoah|Last shot fired]] June 22, 1865.}}<ref name=\"NYT JD Cap\">{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1865/05/10/archives/important-proclamations-the-belligerent-rights-of-the-rebels-at-an.html|title=The Belligerent Rights of the Rebels at an End. All Nations Warned Against Harboring Their Privateers. If They Do Their Ships Will be Excluded from Our Ports. Restoration of Law in the State of Virginia. The Machinery of Government to be Put in Motion There |website=The New York Times|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=May 10, 1865|accessdate=December 23, 2013}}</ref><br> \n| place       = [[Southern United States]], [[Northeastern United States]], [[Western United States]], [[Atlantic Ocean]]\n| result      = [[Union (American Civil War)|Union]] victory:{{bulleted list|Dissolution of the [[Confederate States of America|Confederate States]]|U.S. [[territorial integrity]] preserved|[[Slavery in the United States|Slavery]] [[Thirteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|abolished]]|Beginning of the [[Reconstruction era]]|Passage and ratification of the [[Reconstruction Amendments|13th, 14th and 15th amendments]] to the [[Constitution of the United States]]}}\n| combatant1  = <center>'''[[Union (American Civil War)|Union]]'''</center>\n