oliticians, Slavery Extension, and the Coming of the Civil War | year= 2005 | publisher= Hill and Wang | location= New York |isbn= 978-0-8090-4439-9}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last1= Holzer|first1=Harold|last2=Gabbard |first2=Sara Vaughn |title=Lincoln and Freedom: Slavery, Emancipation, and the Thirteenth Amendment|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=xLbkXsn6xHAC|page=174}}|year=2007|location=Carbondale, Illinois|publisher=Southern Illinois University Press|isbn=978-0-8093-2764-5}}\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |last= Huddleston |first= John |title= Killing Ground: The Civil War and the Changing American Landscape |publisher= Johns Hopkins University Press |year= 2002 |location= Baltimore, Maryland |isbn= 978-0-8018-6773-6 |url-access= registration |url= https://archive.org/details/killinggroundpho0000hudd }}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv | last= Johannsen | first= Robert W. | title= Stephen A. Douglas | year= 1973 | publisher= Oxford University Press| location= New York |isbn= 978-0-19-501620-8}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last= Johnson|first= Timothy D.|title= Winfield Scott: The Quest for Military Glory|publisher=University Press of Kansas |year= 1998 |location= Lawrence, Kansas|isbn= 978-0-7006-0914-7}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last1=Jones|first1=Howard|title=Abraham Lincoln and a New Birth of Freedom: The Union and Slavery in the Diplomacy of the Civil War|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=gVvZb5oeVtwC}}|year=1999 |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |location= Lincoln, Nebraska |isbn=978-0-8032-2582-4}}\n* {{cite book| ref= harv |last=Jones|first=Howard|title=Crucible of Power: A History of American Foreign Relations to 1913|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=TFyLOUrdGFwC|page=225}}|year=2002|location=Wilmington, Delaware|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=978-0-8420-2916-2}}\n* {{cite book | ref= harv | last= Keegan | first= John | title= The American Civil War: A Military History | year= 2009 | publisher= Alfred A. Knopf | location= New York | isbn= 978-0-3