ory]]\n* {{cite EB1911|wstitle=American Civil War |short=x}}\n* {{Cite book|url={{google books |plainurl=y |id=XWyKZwEACAAJ}}|title=The Artillery Service in the War of the Rebellion, 1861\u201365|last=Tidball|first=John C.|date=2011|publisher=Westholme Publishing|isbn=9781594161490|language=en}}\n*The Civil War: A Visual History, [[DK (publisher)|DK]] 2011\n*Weeks, Michael. The Complete Civil War Road Trip Guide: More than 500 Sites from Gettysburg to Vicksburg   Countryman Press 2016\n*Shaara ,Jeff. Civil War Battlefields: Discovering America's Hallowed Ground Ballantine Books 2006\n*Edwards,F Laura. A Legal History of the Civil War and Reconstruction: A Nation of Rights  Cambridge University Press 2015 \n*McPherson,M James. The War That Forged a Nation: Why the Civil War Still Matters Oxford University Press 2017\n\n==External links==\n<!--Please:\n1) Follow the [[WP:EL]] guideline where possible and consider discussing on the talk page;\n2) Do not turn these bullets into headers! They expand the TOC too much-->\n* {{curlie|Society/History/By_Region/North_America/United_States/Wars/Civil_War/|American Civil War}}\n* [https://westpoint.edu/academics/academic-departments/history/american-civil-war West Point Atlas of Civil War Battles]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160818205335/http://www.archives.gov/research/civil-war/photos/index.html Civil War photos] at the [[National Archives and Records Administration|National Archives]]\n* [https://www.loc.gov/pictures/search?st=grid&c=100&co=cwp View images] from the [https://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/cwp/ Civil War Photographs Collection] at the Library of Congress\n* [http://www.battlefields.org/ American Battlefield Trust] A non-profit land preservation and educational organization with two divisions, the Civil War Trust and the Revolutionary War Trust, dedicated to preserving America's battlefields through land acquisitions.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090811064152/http://www.gettysburg.edu/library/gettdigital/civil_war/civilwar.htm Civil War Era Digital Collection at Gettysburg College] This collection contains digital images of political cartoons, personal papers, pamphlets, maps, paintings and photographs from the Civil War Era held in Special Collections at Gettysburg College.\n* [https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/civil-war Civil War 150] ''Washington Post'' interactive website on the 150th Anniversary of the American Civil War.\n* [http://www.american-south.org/ Civil War in the American South] \u2013 An Association of Southeastern Research Libraries (ASERL) portal with links to almost 9,000 digitized Civil War-era items\u2014books, pamphlets, broadsides, letters, maps, personal papers, and manuscripts\u2014held at ASERL member libraries\n* [http://www.sonofthesouth.net/ The Civil War] \u2013 site with 7,000 pages, including the complete run of Harper's Weekly newspapers from the Civil War\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=gov.archives.arc.54756|name=A House Divided (1960)}}\n* [https://persuasivemaps.library.cornell.edu/browse-subject \"American Civil World\" maps at the Persuasive Cartography, The PJ Mode Collection], [[Cornell University Library]]\n* [http://www.shapell.org/Collection/Civil-War Civil War Manuscripts]\n\n<br /><!--this break is to put visual space between the last information and the following template if needed-->\n\n{{American Civil War}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Articles related to the American Civil War\n|list1=\n{{Foreign countries in the American Civil War}}\n{{American conflicts}}\n{{United States topics}}\n}}\n\n{{subject bar |wikt=y |commons=y |n=y |q=y |s=y |b=y |voy=y |v=y |portal1=American Civil War}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:American Civil War| ]]<!--please leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Rebellions in the United States]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1861]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1862]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1863]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1864]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1865]]\n[[Category:19th-