{"title_page": "Domingo Villar", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=February 2016}}\n\n'''Domingo Villar''' (born 1971) is a [[Spaniards|Spanish]] crime writer. He was born and raised in [[Vigo]], [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]] and now lives in Madrid. He has published two acclaimed bestsellers featuring Inspector Leo Caldas, a dyed-in-the-wool Galician detective, and Rafael Est\u00e9vez, his down to earth assistant from Zaragoza who finds it difficult to cope with the Galician sense of irony. Both novels were originally published in [[Galician language|Galician]] before being translated into [[Spanish language|Spanish]] by the author himself. They have also been translated into several other European languages.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.littlebrown.co.uk/authors/detail.page?id=IQxbVixFOKNItGgKmBUslVEtCEvwmdM5HdX-IzZ4CZc0nuMqLGZ61bffwL1b|title=Domingo Villar - Little, Brown Book Group|website=littlebrown.co.uk|access-date=2016-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115082656/https://www.littlebrown.co.uk/authors/detail.page?id=IQxbVixFOKNItGgKmBUslVEtCEvwmdM5HdX-IzZ4CZc0nuMqLGZ61bffwL1b|archive-date=2017-11-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n2006: Ojos de agua (Spanish)\n*(Galician: Ollos de auga)\n*(English : Water-blue eyes, tr. Martin Schifino)\n*(German: Wasserblaue Augen, tr. Peter Kultzen)\n*(Italian: Occhi di acqua, tr. S. Sichel)\n*(Swedish: Nattens m\u00f6rka toner: Ett fall f\u00f6r kommissarie Leo Caldas, tr. Lena E. Heyman)\n\n2009:  La playa de los ahogados\n*(Galician: A praia dos afogados)\n*(English: Death on a Galician shore, tr. Sonia Soto) \n*(German: Strand der Ertrunkenen, tr. Carsten Regling)\n*(Swedish: De drunknades strand, tr. Lena E. Heyman)\n*(French: La plage des noy\u00e9s, tr. Dominique Lepreux)\n\nLa playa de los ahogados was brought to the screen in 2015 by the director [[Gerardo Herrero]], based on a filmscript by the author.<ref>[http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-228823/trailer-19541778/ Extract from the film -]</ref>\n\n== Prizes ==\n* Premio Sintagma (2007)<ref>El escritor Domingo Villar obtiene el I Premio Sintagma con la novela 'Ojos de agua' \u2013 [http://www.europapress.es/cultura/noticia-escritor-domingo-villar-obtiene-premio-sintagma-novela-ojos-agua-20071220183656.html]</ref>\n* Premio Ant\u00f3n Losada Di\u00e9guez (2010)<ref>El premio Losada Di\u00e9guez ha reca\u00eddo en Carpintero y Domingo Villar - [https://web.archive.org/web/20100430125126/http://www.laregion.es/noticia/123178/premio/losada/dieguez La Region (gal)]</ref>\n* Libro del a\u00f1o por la Federaci\u00f3n de Libreros de Galicia (2010)<ref>Los libreros entregaron los premios Irmandade do libro - [https://web.archive.org/web/20140221213349/http://librarias.org/es/noticia.php?idnoticia=210 Federaci\u00f3n de Libreros de Galicia]</ref>\n* Premio Brigada 21 for best novel published in Spanish (2009)<ref>\u201cLa playa de los ahogados\u201d, de Domingo Villar, obtiene el Premio Brigada 21 - [https://web.archive.org/web/20121113155248/http://www.periodistas-es.org/libros-y-publicaciones/la-playa-de-los-ahogados-de-domingo-villar-obtiene-el-premio-brigada-21 Periodistas en espa\u00f1ol]</ref>\n* XXV Premio Nacional \"Cultura viva\" Narrativa (2016)<ref>[http://diario16.com/domingo-villar-premio-cultura-viva-de-narrativa Domingo Villar, premio Cultura Viva de Narrativa -]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Villar, Domingo}}\n[[Category:Spanish writers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n\n\n{{spain-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=February 2016}}\n\n'''Domingo Villar''' (born 1971) is a [[Spaniards|Spanish]] crime writer. He was born and raised in [[Vigo]], [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]] and now lives in Madrid. He has published two acclaimed bestsellers featuring Inspector Leo Caldas, a dyed-in-the-wool Galician detective, and Rafael Est\u00e9vez, his down to earth assistant from Zaragoza who finds it difficult to cope with the Galician sense of irony. Both novels were originally published in [[Galician language|Galician]] before being translated into [[Spanish language|Spanish]] by the author himself. They have also been translated into several other European languages.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.littlebrown.co.uk/authors/detail.page?id=IQxbVixFOKNItGgKmBUslVEtCEvwmdM5HdX-IzZ4CZc0nuMqLGZ61bffwL1b|title=Domingo Villar - Little, Brown Book Group|website=littlebrown.co.uk|access-date=2016-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171115082656/https://www.littlebrown.co.uk/authors/detail.page?id=IQxbVixFOKNItGgKmBUslVEtCEvwmdM5HdX-IzZ4CZc0nuMqLGZ61bffwL1b|archive-date=2017-11-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n\n2006: Ojos de agua (Spanish)\n*(Galician: Ollos de auga)\n*(English : Water-blue eyes, tr. Martin Schifino)\n*(German: Wasserblaue Augen, tr. Peter Kultzen)\n*(Italian: Occhi di acqua, tr. S. Sichel)\n*(Swedish: Nattens m\u00f6rka toner: Ett fall f\u00f6r kommissarie Leo Caldas, tr. Lena E. Heyman)\n\n2009:  La playa de los ahogados\n*(Galician: A praia dos afogados)\n*(English: Death on a Galician shore, tr. Sonia Soto) \n*(German: Strand der Ertrunkenen, tr. Carsten Regling)\n*(Swedish: De drunknades strand, tr. Lena E. Heyman)\n*(French: La plage des noy\u00e9s, tr. Dominique Lepreux)\n\nLa playa de los ahogados was brought to the screen in 2015 by the director [[Gerardo Herrero]], based on a filmscript by the author.<ref>Extract from the film -  [http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-228823/trailer-19541778/]</ref>\n\n== Prizes ==\n* Premio Sintagma (2007)<ref>El escritor Domingo Villar obtiene el I Premio Sintagma con la novela 'Ojos de agua' \u2013 [http://www.europapress.es/cultura/noticia-escritor-domingo-villar-obtiene-premio-sintagma-novela-ojos-agua-20071220183656.html]</ref>\n* Premio Ant\u00f3n Losada Di\u00e9guez (2010)<ref>El premio Losada Di\u00e9guez ha reca\u00eddo en Carpintero y Domingo Villar - [https://web.archive.org/web/20100430125126/h